<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-21T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/983: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-21T13:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1937—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. For Braden. Your 147, August 20, 8 p.m. The following telegram has
                            been sent to the Legation at Asunción: (Here quote telegram to
                            Am[erican] Legation, Asunción.<note n="19" xml:id="d718fn19"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>)</p>
                        <p>Please communicate with Howard by telephone as soon as possible and
                            telegraph the Department the results of your conversation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>